PN,31602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1782398898
OL,3,CParents of 11-year-old boy who drowned
OL,4,Cwarn against open water swimming
OL,6,FIt comes as the record was broken for
OL,7,Fthe hottest ever June day on
OL,8,FWednesday, with rare red warnings in
OL,9,Fplace for extreme heat across parts of
OL,10,Fthe country.
OL,12,FMackenzie Swift, from Mexborough in
OL,13,FSouth Yorkshire, was the youngest of
OL,14,Fthe 19 people to die during the hot
OL,15,Fweather in May.
OL,17,FMackenzie and a friend had cycled to
OL,18,Fan area known locally as pebble beach
OL,19,Fon the River Don. His body was found
OL,20,Ftwo days later.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1782398898
OL,3,CParents of 11-year-old boy who drowned
OL,4,Cwarn against open water swimming
OL,6,FHis mum, Suzie Gough, told ITV News
OL,7,Fshe never thought her "sensitive,
OL,8,Ffunny boy" would go to the river.
OL,10,F"They just kept saying we haven't
OL,11,Ffound him, we haven't found him," she
OL,12,Frecalled.
OL,14,F"It was so not like him to just go
OL,15,Fdown to the river and then to not come
OL,16,Fback - I wouldn't wish it on anybody."
OL,26,@rD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1782398898
OL,3,CParents of 11-year-old boy who drowned
OL,4,Cwarn against open water swimming
OL,6,FHis dad, Michael Swift, said: "My
OL,7,Fbiggest fear was that he'd gone in
OL,8,F(the water) and as it got later and
OL,9,Flater, I thought to myself, if he
OL,10,Fdoesn't come out tonight, he'll come
OL,11,Fout eventually, but he won't come out
OL,12,Fand be with us again."
OL,14,FThey are now campaigning for greater
OL,15,Fawareness of water safety, and say
OL,16,Fthat if it doesn't come before the
OL,17,Fsummer holidays, more children will
OL,18,Fdie.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1782398898
OL,3,CParents of 11-year-old boy who drowned
OL,4,Cwarn against open water swimming
OL,6,FMichael said: "It might look safe, but
OL,7,Fit's really not. Go to your local
OL,8,Fleisure centre, not down the river.
OL,9,FNobody knows what is in there."
OL,11,FDale Coles was a family friend
OL,12,Finvolved in the search for Mackenzie.
OL,14,FHe said: "In the back of your mind,
OL,15,Fyou always think it can't be true. It
OL,16,Fcan't be my friend's child.
OL,18,F"I said we need to fetch him and take
OL,19,Fhim home to his mum and dad no matter
OL,20,Fwhat.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1782398898
OL,3,CParents of 11-year-old boy who drowned
OL,4,Cwarn against open water swimming
OL,6,F"You're never going to stop all kids,
OL,7,Fbut the more we can get into their
OL,8,Fheads, the more we can help. If we
OL,9,Fsave one life, then that's an impact."
OL,11,FThat wish to save lives is echoed by
OL,12,Fthe family of Sam Haycock, who drowned
OL,13,Ffive years ago also in South Yorkshire.
OL,15,FSam, 16, died at the Ulley Reservoir
OL,16,Fwhile celebrating the end of his GCSEs
OL,17,Fin 2021, and his father Simon has been
OL,18,Fcampaigning for better education and
OL,19,Frescue equipment ever since.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1782398898
OL,3,CParents of 11-year-old boy who drowned
OL,4,Cwarn against open water swimming
OL,6,FThe two families met up to discuss
OL,7,Ftheir shared goals.
OL,9,FMeeting Mackenzie's parents for the
OL,10,Ffirst time was a reminder to Simon of
OL,11,Fthe heartache a heatwave can cause -
OL,12,Fand the work that needs to be done.
OL,14,F"We do a lot of work educating
OL,15,Fchildren and raising money to buy
OL,16,Flifesaving equipment, but we often see
OL,17,Fthat equipment is being vandalised or
OL,18,Fdamaged, so we need a really strong
OL,19,Flaw that protects it," he told ITV
OL,20,FNews.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
